President Trump held a press conference in the Roosevelt Room of the White House to discuss the grounding of Boeing 737 MAX aircraft following the Ethiopian Airlines crash. The Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) will issue an emergency order to ground all flights of the 737 MAX 8 and 737 MAX 9 planes. The President spoke with Elaine Chao, Secretary of Transportation, Dan Elwell, Acting Administrator of the FAA, and Dennis Muilenburg, CEO of Boeing, who all agreed with the decision. The planes will be grounded until further notice, and pilots and airlines have been notified. President Trump also mentioned that the press conference was originally planned to discuss drug trafficking and border security. He thanked federal, state, and local leaders for their efforts in combating drug traffickers and criminal cartels at the southern border. The President expressed concern over the flow of illegal drugs into the United States and the impact it has on society. He emphasized the need for border security and reiterated his commitment to building a wall. The President also addressed questions about the sentencing of Paul Manafort, the China trade deal, and the Mueller Report.